Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
specifyPartition(25.10)                                specifyPartition(25.10)

Name
       specifyPartition - Loads the partition specification file

Syntax
       specifyPartition

       [-help]

       <partitionSpecFileName>

       [-noEqualizePtnHInst]

       Loads  the  partition  specification  file. The partition specification
       file is created from the Specify Partition form. You can use this  com-
       mand after importing the design.

       Note: You can create partitions inside power domains as well.

       Note:  Command  specifyPartition is now obsolete and will be removed in
       the next major release of the software. This command has been  replaced
       by the definePartition command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each specifyPartition parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man specifyPartition

       -noEqualizePtnHInst
              Disables the snapping capability of the clone partitions to  the
              power  grid,  such  that clones do not necessarily have the same
              row structure and pattern as their master.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       <partitionSpecFileName>
              Specifies the file containing the partition specification.

              Data_type: string, required

Example
       The following command loads the partition specification  file  app1.ptn
       and updates the Floorplan view:

       specifyPartition app1_p.ptn

